<br>
I rely heavily on my draughts and usually have no problem chain casting this just about through the fight while throwing in a few of my big bang - currently AT - to spice things up.  From my point of view, I can spread my damage out over time and in the event of AE's to hide from I can cast faster and get my damage off with good consistency.<br>
<br>
Other wizards I know have been talking about trouble controling agro after the last patch still and I noticed that they rely on their big bangs to do their work.  I'm not saying this is the agro problem, I'm just saying that these are the things I notice them saying consistently.<br>
<br>
Now I am not doing less damage than them, however my spell casts faster and I can keep casting it without interruption.  I'm just wondering how you guys do it.<br>
