<br>
On PoP mobs that aren't very magic resistant, or when my raid/party has a good debuffing class, I make sure to load Telekin.  Telekin generates substantial aggro, but since PoP mob DPS can be so great, the ability to prevent the mob from delivering damage for 8 seconds is remarkable.  Not only will this enable you to potentially save the life of party members that take aggro from the tank (slowers, etc.), but it enables you to save healer mana by preventing the mob from delivering damage at all, while your raid/party is still doing damage to it.  I never cast this spell unless I KNOW that I will not draw the target's attention if the Telekin is resisted, unless of course I am trying to save the life of the cleric at the cost of my own.<br>
<br>
I have trained Quick Damage III and usually have a Mage summoned Spell Haste IV ring.  When I have Blessing of Reverence I cast Agnarr's Thunder in 4.6 seconds.  These benefits allow me to generate higher DPS with Agnarr's than with draughts once aggro has been sufficiently stabilized by the main tank.  Again, the resistance of the target mob is always the deciding factor.  It makes no sense to use Ice Spear, even though it is my most efficient nuke (when amplified by IceFlame of Ec'i), if it is just as likely to be resisted as not.  When resists aren't a factor, using Ice Spear and Agnarr's are a clear advantage in terms of DPS.  To control aggro I simply use Concussion or click my Mana Robe in the time I have saved by using larger nukes that have a reduced casting time.<br>
<br>
Draughts are unquestionablly the most RELIABLE damage.  The aggro they generate is in small enough &quot;chunks&quot; on a pretty even interval that it is easy to avoid getting the attention of the target.  The -50 to resistance modifier ensures more consistent damage to the target.  The fast cast time makes the spell easy to channel.  These are the best spells we have for all of these reasons, and are the spells we can land most safely without drawing aggro at the beginning of an encounter.<br>
<br>
Larger nukes are beneficial mid fight because by this time sufficient aggro has been generated by the Main Tank that if all of the nukers unload massive damage all at once, the mob is more likely to die than it is to aggro on one of them.  Large nukes that land simultaneously can kill a mob before it even gets a chance to enrage, which again can help save cleric mana.<br>
<br>
With all of this in mind, my typical strategy is to open with a draught or Ice Spear, reduce my aggro with Concussion or by clicking my Mana Robe, followed by either Telekin or a larger nuke.  If the target is particularly resistant, simply chaining Draughts is the most reliable and efficient way to nuke, but typically I find my mana pool and mana regeneration to be greater than the cleric of my raid/party...so using less efficent, higher DPS, higher RISK nukes sometimes provides an advantage which is justified.<br>
<br>
If you are grouping with other Wizards it is very beneficial to announce a successful landing of Telekin (make a separate chat channel for these announcements and have the Wizards join it).  By doing this it is possible to keep a rotation whereby the target is kept stunned repeatedly.  Especially against targets that hit for high damage, this proves to be a very powerful strategy that can save the cleric considerable mana.<br>
<br>
In some circumstances you may find rain spells to be very efficient, but I find once you get to lvl 60+, simply using Sunstrike or the PoP nukes is far more reliable damage.  It all really depends on the target and the debuffs used. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tazmanndvill>tazmanndvill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/16/03 1:04:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=25986.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How do you burn?</span><hr size=1> Big bangs are always fun.<br>
