<br>
When I play them together, I have to switch back and forth between windows, which is cumbersome.  I have gotten used to it and can now do it pretty quick, but it severely reduces my ability to just stand there and chain cast with my wizard, while trying to keep my ranger in melee range of the mob... due to melee-push.<br>
<br>
So what I do is focus on keeping my ranger in melee range, and just switch over to my wizard (who sits on a horse so I don't have to stand up and sit down repeatedly, and allows me to med while I goof off with my ranger) to cast a nuke.  I choose big nukes (Ice Comet) over Draughts because I can't stand there and Draught repeatedly while keeping the ranger in melee range.  Get ranger in range, switch to wizard, cast Ice Comet, switch back to ranger and keep slashing away.  8 secs later watch a huge comet of ice land on the mobs head... lather, rinse, repeat.<br>
<br>
This allows me to do significant damage with my wizzie while not losing melee damage with my ranger.  I know it's not as effective from a wizard stand-point if I'm not Draughting and Concussing... but an epic ranger together with 80% of a wizard is more than no epic ranger and 100% wizard.  I do more damage overall this way.<br>
<br>
But if I'm just playing my wizard and not 2-boxing the ranger, I use Draughts and Concussion, and just hammer it.  At level 54, Voltaic Draught and Draught of Fire have the best mana ratios... including over Ice Comet.<br>
<br>
